lysis of Algorithms, suggesting a modest gap in deep mathematical rigor and algorithmic analysis. Overall, Ryan’s transcript reflects a high level of competence and readiness for advanced graduate work in CS, especially in systems and software engineering domains."}, "class_anti_skills": [{"class": "CS 161 – DESIGN AND ANALYSIS OF ALGORITHMS", "reason": "Earned a B+, the lowest grade among core CS courses, indicating a relative weakness in rigorous algorithm design and analysis.", "skills": ["Algorithmic analysis", "Advanced problem solving"]}, {"class": "MATH 51 – LINEAR ALGEBRA, MULTIVARIABLE CALCULUS, AND MODERN APPLICATIONS", "reason": "Received a B, suggesting a modest shortfall in the mathematical foundations that support many advanced CS topics.", "skills": ["Mathematical modeling", "Linear algebra foundations"]}]}', NULL, NULL, '2026-03-08 01:16:42.012167+00'),
